commit.message:
Allow quoting to preserve spaces in the login option in config file

There are three ways to quote supported, derived from shell quoting.

- Without surrounding quotes, backspace unconditionally escapes the
  following character. `\ ` is parsed as a single space which does not
  separate words.
- Within double quotes, backspace only escapes backspace and double
  quotes. `"\\"` is parsed as a single backslash, while `"\b"` is parsed
  as the two characters backslash and 'b'. All white space is preserved
  within quotes.
- Within single quotes, backspace does not work as an escape character.
  `'\"'` is parsed as the two characters backslash and dobule quote.
  All white space is preserved within quotes.

Fixes #57

commit.message:
Make code sent by backspace key configurable

Keep the default code as ASCII backspace, but allow setting the code to
ASCII delete. This is the code used by the Linux console and most modern
terminal emulators by default.

This depends on a corresponding change in libtsm.

commit.message:
Properly handle multiple possible EGL configs

The current code assumes the first returned EGL context will work (only
requests one). There are some cases where this does not work, due to an
incompatibility with the format used. When this occurs, kmscon will fail
to paint anything, and you'll see this in the logs (with EGL debug
logging on):

```
May 30 14:40:53 Argon kmscon[3071]: libEGL debug: EGL user error 0x3009
(EGL_BAD_MATCH) in eglCreateWindowSurface: EGL config not compatible
with GBM format
May 30 14:40:53 Argon kmscon[3071]: [0002.774416] ERROR:
uterm_drm3d_video: cannot create EGL window surface (display_activate()
in src/uterm_drm3d_video.c:180)
```

This makes the config selection code pull all matching configs, then
filter based on matching formats. After this change, kmscon succesfully
loads.
Add unifont binary source and clangd compile config to .gitignore
